  "question": "What is the total household spend once VAT is added?",
  "options": [
   "£84",
   "£484",
   "£534",
   "£576"
  ],
  "caseStudy": "<p>VAT on most food products is 20%. VAT on fresh fruit is 8%. A household spends £400 on food products and £50 on fresh fruit.</p>",
  "hint": "Apply each VAT rate to its own item, then add BOTH totals together — the question asks for the total SPEND, not the tax.",
  "starter": "The correct answer is...",
